<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-06-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 583.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-06-17"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 17, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 2d instant, No. 479,
                            respecting the proceedings of Mr. de la Montagnie, the United States
                            consul at Nantes, with regard to the <pb facs="0126" n="106" xml:id="pg_106"/> insurgent ships in course of construction at that
                            place, has been received. We shall write to Mr. Montagnie and relieve
                            him from the censure, and at the same time shall tell him that he was
                            right in addressing himself to you.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>